11.Oct.2019 - 3.02AM
//Variables are simply containers that store values
//They follow this pattern:
var yourVariableName = yourValue;

//They can store all of the values we've seen
var name = 'Rusty';
var secretNumber = 73;
var isAdorable = true;

//Recall the stored value by calling the variable name
var name = 'Rusty';
"hello there " + name //"hello there Rusty"

var num = 37;
num + 3 + 10 //50

//We can also update existing variables
var name = "Robert";
name = "Bob";

JS cases should be camelCase, (another ones are snake_case and kebab-case for variables but JavaScript cases should be camelCase)
ex: var secretNumber = 73;
